/target
Cargo.lock
# ...but experiment/ is a BINARY, not a library: the paper's numbers have to
# reproduce from a command in this repo, and that needs its deps pinned. The
# rule above is unanchored, so it would swallow this lock without the negation.
!experiment/Cargo.lock
# The release workflow extracts the tag's notes here. Ignored so cargo's
# dirty-tree check (which counts untracked files) cannot fail the publish.
/NOTES.md

# CARGO_REGISTRY_TOKEN for a local `scripts/publish.sh --execute` — the resume
# path when CI's rate limit outlasts a job. Same dirty-tree reason as above.
/.env

# The M6 trainer byte-compiles in CI; keep its cache out of the tree.
__pycache__/
